On May 18, 2018, President Donald J. Trump issued a proclamation expressing condolences for the shooting at Santa Fe High School in Texas. The proclamation orders that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff at the White House, public buildings, military posts, naval stations, and naval vessels until May 22, 2018. The flag will also be flown at half-staff at all United States embassies, consular offices, and military facilities abroad for the same length of time.